<body>
    <h1>Task 16 - RAD</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 local-id=3D"77685faf042b" id=3D"Task16-RAD-1.Introduction">1. I=
ntroduction</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"155205c6b2e9" id=3D"Task16-RAD-1.1Purpose">1.1 Purpose</h3>
<p local-id=3D"d93446dfd15b">The purpose of this document is to define the =
requirements for deploying and managing a scalable Flask-based web applicat=
ion using AWS cloud services.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c378a8509f33">This document is intended for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"896a01cc3daf">DevOps Engineers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"82c33aa94c4f">Developers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"17871e5163b3">Project Evaluators</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"02eb0cfd4181">System Administrators</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"18a1d0524a44" id=3D"Task16-RAD-1.2Scope">1.2 Scope</h3>
<p local-id=3D"f626857558e9"><strong>Included in scope:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5100b442f1b4">Deployment of Flask application on EC2 instanc=
es</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"684ca957957b">Load balancing using Application Load Balancer=
 (ALB)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3ecb6c48c205">Automation using AWS SSM Run Command</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"31cb1cd04293">Integration with MongoDB Atlas</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8b6f21d584b7">High availability setup across multiple AZs</p=
></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"7ef3ec03e1dd"><strong>Not included:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"98f1fd53d698">Frontend development</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7391b85994e8">CI/CD pipeline tools (like Jenkins/GitHub Acti=
ons)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dfa34c010af7">Advanced monitoring tools (CloudWatch detailed=
 setup not included)</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"9b189b33aab0" id=3D"Task16-RAD-1.3Definitions,Acronyms,andA=
bbreviations">1.3 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"d3=
af930c-5911-417e-ad04-0fe3bcfcef7b" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"668162454d10">Term</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"d887b28ea864">Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bda8e5e17285">EC2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"61d0355ba35e">Elastic Compute Cloud</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3d185b3f8179">ALB</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f7cbfa4392e1">Application Load Balancer</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"de0dc6aadba1">SSM</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dad9628a4bf8">AWS Systems Manager</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"76832fa7a7f5">AZ</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"edc84109375d">Availability Zone</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d9d97e0754ee">API</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0ea44f209ffe">Application Programming Interface</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bf310e33592b">DB</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"234b8f9dd2ad">Database</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"77d55096c6b7">MongoDB Atlas</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ea4d7b5f9fbb">Cloud-hosted MongoDB service</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"3234a01ac634" id=3D"Task16-RAD-1.4References">1.4 Reference=
s</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"20318afeb571">AWS Documentation (EC2, ALB, SSM)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bd24b9ae6372">MongoDB Atlas Documentation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c836ebdbb984">Flask Framework Documentation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"66ef90a9508f">GitHub Repository: FlaskWithMongoDB</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"6959ffdadc68" id=3D"Task16-RAD-1.5Overview">1.5 Overview</h=
3>
<p local-id=3D"59696a0ead17">This document describes:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e54c119e7891">System architecture</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bf06caedf1d7">Functional &amp; non-functional requirements</=
p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f7ff61f187bb">Use cases</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2b0dd2a51cca">Risks and constraints</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7fc8e53b553b">Deployment and automation flow</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"90818689b069" id=3D"Task16-RAD-2.ProjectOverview">2. Projec=
t Overview</h1>
<h3 local-id=3D"f39e9224324a" id=3D"Task16-RAD-2.1ProjectObjectives">2.1 Pr=
oject Objectives</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ea015c0d4207">Deploy a Flask application on AWS EC2 instance=
s</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e799a22deb8e">Ensure high availability using ALB</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cba4deafc279">Automate deployment using SSM</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"898c9dcdcbaf">Use MongoDB Atlas for managed database</p></li=
>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e798898d52db">Achieve scalable and reliable system</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"2f74abb3e5b8" id=3D"Task16-RAD-2.2BusinessGoals">2.2 Busine=
ss Goals</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c41ea2142697">Reduce downtime using load balancing</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3577d567fba0">Improve scalability of application</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6ae1108ffc1f">Automate deployment to save time</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f441cacef0a5">Use managed DB to reduce maintenance cost</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f05c8f523a46">Ensure secure and efficient architecture</p></=
li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"282b3debaf05" id=3D"Task16-RAD-2.3Background">2.3 Backgroun=
d</h3>
<p local-id=3D"4c6101cb0aa1">Traditionally, applications were deployed on a=
 single server, leading to:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"98560e6ea05c">Downtime issues</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"83686e7e1dfb">Poor scalability</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d6c7cfa5809e">Manual deployment</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"d04a124567b1">This project solves these issues by using:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5c2b12b97db4">Cloud infrastructure (AWS)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"52d5896ed1ff">Automation tools (SSM)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"553f830ada54">Managed database (MongoDB Atlas)</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"5b8233ee4551" id=3D"Task16-RAD-2.4Constraints">2.4 Constrai=
nts</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5a1730fdea49">Limited AWS free-tier resources</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b1c7646f21b4">Budget constraints</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"830d6429c4ab">Dependency on internet connectivity</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bed0d7601703">Learning curve for AWS services</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"529e7be80007" id=3D"Task16-RAD-3.FunctionalRequirements">3.=
 Functional Requirements</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"6cc521a9f05c" id=3D"Task16-RAD-3.1UseCaseDiagram">3.1 Use C=
ase Diagram</h2><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-cente=
r-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedde=
d-image image-center" alt=3D"image (2)-20260321-124938.jpg" width=3D"468" l=
oading=3D"lazy" src=3D"7787a2acfd1ee99fbf6d6ad3a7cc9edab876c35eb0b875d21f3e=
11db1fe8b781" data-image-src=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki/download/=
attachments/1856700424/image%20(2)-20260321-124938.jpg?version=3D1&amp;modi=
ficationDate=3D1774097407235&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=
=3D"421" data-width=3D"1001" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linke=
d-resource-id=3D"1886257168" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked=
-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image (=
2)-20260321-124938.jpg" data-base-url=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki"=
 data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/jpeg" data-linked-resource-cont=
ainer-id=3D"1856700424" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" data-m=
edia-id=3D"ca5d1536-220a-4d1f-9ca8-f223cb825e1f" data-media-type=3D"file" h=
eight=3D"196"></span>
<h2 local-id=3D"b85e4bdc9267" id=3D"Task16-RAD-3.2UseCases">3.2 Use Cases</=
h2>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"302b804c7fb0" id=3D"Task16-RAD-3.2.1UseCase1:AccessFlaskApp=
viaALB">3.2.1 Use Case 1: Access Flask App via ALB</h3>
<p local-id=3D"56107170fb83"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
User accesses the Flask application through the Application Load Balancer.<=
/p>
<p local-id=3D"573e6deffc5e"><strong>Actors:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ab93270f9641">User</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"1cd682858d10"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b058501266ec">ALB is configured</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e34f97cd701c">EC2 instances are running</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b528674e8532">Flask app is deployed</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"ca9f97c774c7"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"eba4a875ff40">User receives response from Flask app</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"5995be1de4f5"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d550ca3029a8">User enters ALB DNS in browser</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"261362530146">Request goes to ALB</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9e6537db226a">ALB forwards request to one EC2 instance</p></=
li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"96681db4d083">Flask app processes request</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5e9878dba440">Response is returned to user</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"a78ef6232ec7"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"52a758affcbe">If one EC2 fails =E2=86=92 ALB routes to anoth=
er instance</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"97f8595d2221" id=3D"Task16-RAD-3.2.2UseCase2:LoadBalanceTra=
fficAcrossEC2">3.2.2 Use Case 2: Load Balance Traffic Across EC2</h3>
<p local-id=3D"caa3b1cca4d1"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
Distribute incoming traffic across multiple EC2 instances.</p>
<p local-id=3D"6b08d17a106d"><strong>Actors:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7563d9cb809e">System (ALB)</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"cd1b405b5a58"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"50125eca3f3d">Target group configured</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"15cb2d960034">Health checks enabled</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f87e8be0c789"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f01046ade7dc">Traffic is evenly distributed</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"ae4e5005a623"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f6e708b2481c">ALB receives request</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"26ac59d74bb1">Checks healthy instances</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"83259ceff8f6">Routes request to one instance</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e5ff0fbb0617">Maintains load balance</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"382321eb742b"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4b0e610065f9">If instance unhealthy =E2=86=92 removed from r=
outing</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"7c5704f0f243" id=3D"Task16-RAD-3.2.3UseCase3:DeployFlaskApp=
viaSSM">3.2.3 Use Case 3: Deploy Flask App via SSM</h3>
<p local-id=3D"042e5ff6c9b4"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
DevOps engineer deploys or updates Flask app using SSM Run Command.</p>
<p local-id=3D"36944a732de6"><strong>Actors:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8882c55bf839">DevOps Engineer</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"865f073321af"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"23fd4960ef21">EC2 instances connected to SSM</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"49507cfc7750">SSM document created</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"9a6ecd1af88f"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9e7d69237595">Application updated on all EC2 instances</p></=
li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"44f72604c8db"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7031ebf52a51">Engineer triggers SSM Run Command</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b471228a6fd0">System pulls latest code from GitHub</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"415354f30349">Installs dependencies</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"821c1da4b0e4">Restarts Flask service</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1468a8b9a8c3">Logs saved in <code>/var/log/deploy.log</code>=
</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"f25e4fb14144"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bb27ee115d6f">If deployment fails =E2=86=92 error logged</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"761fee7565b2" id=3D"Task16-RAD-3.2.4UseCase4:ManageMongoDBA=
tlasConnection">3.2.4 Use Case 4: Manage MongoDB Atlas Connection</h3>
<p local-id=3D"5ae884dca0ed"><strong>Description:</strong><br>
Application connects to MongoDB Atlas database.</p>
<p local-id=3D"1a1829513d48"><strong>Actors:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"69fe9c6e4713">User</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ccd549eb5515">DevOps Engineer</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"a771368bd931"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2eecbd3b1c07">MongoDB Atlas cluster created</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e400850e4f92">Connection string configured</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"38cc7fdb929e"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"337712d77466">Data stored/retrieved successfully</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2893d2b3f8eb"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"206e06748121">Flask app sends request to DB</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f107c9728cc2">MongoDB Atlas processes query</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6d65f09337b6">Data returned to application</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cef17a3eaba5">User sees result</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"239b2f7ff232"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b14c2b2e8dda">If connection fails =E2=86=92 error returned</=
p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"c9c81a754523" id=3D"Task16-RAD-4.Non-FunctionalRequirements=
">4. Non-Functional Requirements</h1>
<h3 local-id=3D"ce8f9a356050" id=3D"Task16-RAD-4.1PerformanceRequirements">=
4.1 Performance Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"15562228b099">Response time &lt; 2 seconds</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b95f80f95951">Handle multiple concurrent users</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"42f5bf31ef8e">Load balancing ensures smooth traffic</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"31832c17b076" id=3D"Task16-RAD-4.2SecurityRequirements">4.2=
 Security Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a9d43b79fcf7">Only ALB allows public access</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f62fc243a723">EC2 instances are private</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e832d8299e8b">Secure MongoDB connection (URI + authenticatio=
n)</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"c4261cd952a6" id=3D"Task16-RAD-4.3UsabilityRequirements">4.=
3 Usability Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4b45d5023c9c">Simple API access</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e3ddece407c3">Easy deployment using SSM</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3c6e4f09e843">Minimal manual intervention</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"6321af83e5f5" id=3D"Task16-RAD-4.4ReliabilityRequirements">=
4.4 Reliability Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3d0eca343f87">High availability using multiple AZs</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5b316da07d04">Failover support via ALB</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"231a177b8b82">Managed DB ensures backup</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"5cc496e23aad" id=3D"Task16-RAD-4.5ComplianceRequirements">4=
.5 Compliance Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ce735ac2473f">Follow AWS best practices</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ed5c741aa7fc">Secure data handling</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a7f3bc76dce0">Proper access control</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"e95eb83ba63f" id=3D"Task16-RAD-5.AssumptionsandDependencies=
">5. Assumptions and Dependencies</h1>
<h3 local-id=3D"adf15097d5e7" id=3D"Task16-RAD-5.1Assumptions">5.1 Assumpti=
ons</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"844ed4aed531">AWS services are available</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f404bfae6f20">Internet connection is stable</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"49aad438ca25">GitHub repo is accessible</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"77c1da164d5f" id=3D"Task16-RAD-5.2Dependencies">5.2 Depende=
ncies</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"90654d8be835">AWS EC2, ALB, SSM</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8b782ef26d99">MongoDB Atlas</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e64ab5c959c4">Flask application code</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"3a690d04282e" id=3D"Task16-RAD-6.RiskAnalysis">6. Risk Anal=
ysis</h1>
<h3 local-id=3D"e786b6f5c055" id=3D"Task16-RAD-6.1RiskIdentification">6.1 R=
isk Identification</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"07f3c7479f36">EC2 instance failure</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"405a81e78544">Deployment failure</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e017b7d524f9">Database connectivity issues</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f8170a227181">Security misconfiguration</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"9b683ca5769f" id=3D"Task16-RAD-6.2RiskMitigation">6.2 Risk =
Mitigation</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a54af7567129">Use multiple AZs</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"83f7c3825241">Use logs for debugging</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"996b80e9e579">Monitor health checks</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1cc747a7eb7d">Secure configurations properly</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
